<statement>
  <p>[@@@@@@@@@]</p>
  <ol>
    <li>
      <p>
        Write a story to match the equation <m>x + 2\frac{1}{2} = 10</m>.
      </p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p>
        Explain what <m>x</m> represents in your story.
      </p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p>
        Solve the equation. Explain or show your reasoning.
      </p>
    </li>
  </ol>
</statement>

<solution>
  <p>[@@@@@@@@@]</p>
  <ol>
    <li>
      <p>
        Lin likes to bake batches of muffins and share them with friends and family. She needs <m>10</m> cups of flour for her next batch, but only has <m>2\frac{1}{2}</m> cups left. How much more flour does she need?
      </p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p>
        <m>x</m> represents the number of cups of flour Lin needs.
      </p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p>
        <m>x = 7\frac{1}{2}</m>. I subtracted <m>2\frac{1}{2}</m> from each side of the equation.
      </p>
    </li>
  </ol>
</solution>


